 <section id="negotiation" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">4. Pricing & MOQ Negotiation</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Pricing is where many buyers make their second biggest mistake. (The first is not verifying the factory.) A first quote is rarely the best price. Professional buyers typically negotiate 5-15% below the initial quotation. Understanding standard terms helps you negotiate confidently and avoid common pitfalls. Key terms to negotiate with your China charger supplier:</p>
 <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-4">
 <li><strong>FOB vs EXW vs DDP</strong>, FOB Shenzhen is the most common for first orders</li>
 <li><strong>Payment terms</strong>, Standard is 30% deposit, 70% before shipment. Avoid 100% upfront</li>
 <li><strong>MOQ breakdown</strong>, Ask for MOQ per SKU, not just total. Multi-product orders may get lower MOQ</li>
 <li><strong>Sample policy</strong>, Legitimate suppliers offer samples (usually paid, refundable with bulk order)</li>
 <li><strong>Volume discounts</strong>, Negotiate tiered pricing: 500, 1,000, 3,000, 5,000+ units. <a href="/products/gan-charger" class="text-brandBlue font-semibold">See GaN charger wholesale pricing →</a></li>
 </ul>
 <div class="p-6 bg-brandBlue/5 rounded-2xl border border-brandBlue/20">
